o\\n3. **Pattern**: How are paths used? Are they \\\"required reading\\\" lists? Template code? Reference pointers?\\n4. **Hardcoded details besides paths**: Method counts, function signatures, struct field names, specific runner names — anything that could drift from the actual code\\n\\nAlso check: Do the actual directories `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/`, `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/`, `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/` exist? What about `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` and `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md`?\\n\\nFor each file, count how many hardcoded paths there are.\",\"agentId\":\"a831afbd5d59056af\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01KRGy2eG4RirqXXPoVEMePF\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01HiRmvrNYDq9RLfbKB2JnPg\",\"uuid\":\"a9a056fe-7091-4f9e-9ee0-ca8fcdb5d16f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T21:42:52.117Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a9a056fe-7091-4f9e-9ee0-ca8fcdb5d16f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"e3b9b251-e322-4a6b-b48d-361a9097e77a\",\"version\":\"2.1.53\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/agent-integration-skill\",\"slug\":\"merry-leaping-turing\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_018fAYhqhV4svYhnHhPoAu3A\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Probe Command\\n     2→\\n     3→Assess whether a target AI coding agent's hook/lifecycle model is compatible with the Entire CLI before writing any Go code.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Procedure\\n     6→\\n     7→### Phase 1: Architecture Inspection\\n     8→\\n     9→Read these repo files to understand the Entire lifecycle model that the agent must integrate with:\\n    10→\\n    11→**Required reading:**\\n    12→\\n    13→1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — The `Agent` interface (core methods + 6 optional capability interfaces)\\n    14→2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — 7 normalized EventTypes: `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\n    15→3. `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` — How native hook names are registered and routed\\n    16→4. `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — `DispatchLifecycleEvent` handler\\n    17→5. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Full implementation guide\\n    18→6. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Validation criteria\\n    19→\\n    20→**Reference implementations** (read 1-2 for patterns):\\n    21→\\n    22→- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/` — Most complete, has all optional interfaces\\n    23→- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/` — File-watcher based hook model\\n    24→- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/` — Plugin-based hook model\\n    25→\\n    26→Focus on `types.go` (hook input structs), `lifecycle.go` (ParseHookEvent), and `hooks.go` (HookSupport) in each.\\n    27→\\n    28→### Phase 2: Static Capability Checks\\n    29→\\n    30→Non-destructive CLI probing. Record PASS/WARN/FAIL for each:\\n    31→\\n    32→| Check | Command | PASS | FAIL |\\n    33→|-------|---------|------|------|\\n    34→| Binary present | `command -v $AGENT_BIN` | Found | Not found (blocker) |\\n    35→| Help output | `$AGENT_BIN --help` or `$AGENT_BIN help` | Available | No help |\\n    36→| Version info | `$AGENT_BIN --version` or `$AGENT_BIN version` | Available | N/A |\\n    37→| Hook keywords | Scan help for: hook, lifecycle, callback, event, trigger, pre-, post-, plugin, extension | Found | None found |\\n    38→| Session keywords | Scan help for: session, resume, continue, history, transcript, context | Found | None found |\\n    39→| Config directory | Check `~/.$AGENT_SLUG/`, `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/`, `./$AGENT_SLUG/`, `./.${AGENT_SLUG}/` | Found | None found |\\n    40→| Documentation | Web search for hook/plugin/extension docs | Found | None found |\\n    41→\\n    42→### Phase 3: Test Script Creation\\n    43→\\n    44→Based on Phase 2 findings, create an **agent-specific** test script:\\n    45→\\n    46→```\\n    47→scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh\\n    48→```\\n    49→\\n    50→The script is tailored to the specific agent's hook mechanism (not a generic template). Adapt the hook wiring section based on what Phase 2 discovered.\\n    51→\\n    52→**Script structure:**\\n    53→\\n    54→```bash\\n    55→#!/usr/bin/env bash\\n    56→set -euo pipefail\\n    57→\\n    58→AGENT_NAME=\\\"...\\\"\\n    59→AGENT_SLUG=\\\"...\\\"\\n    60→AGENT_BIN=\\\"...\\\"\\n    61→PROBE_DIR=\\\".entire/tmp/probe-${AGENT_SLUG}-$(date +%s)\\\"\\n    62→```\\n    63→\\n    64→**Required sections:**\\n    65→\\n    66→1. **Static checks** — Re-runnable binary/version/help checks\\n    67→2. **Hook wiring** — Create workspace-local config that intercepts hooks and dumps stdin JSON to `$PROBE_DIR/captures/<event-name>-<timestamp>.json`\\n    68→3. **Run modes:**\\n    69→   - `--run-cmd '<cmd>'` — Automated: launch agent, wait, collect\\n    70→   - `--manual-live` — Interactive: user runs agent manually, presses Enter\\n    71→4. **Capture collection** — List and pretty-print all payload files\\n    72→5. **Cleanup** — Restore original config (unless `--keep-config`)\\n    73→6. **Verdict** — PASS/WARN/FAIL per lifecycle event + COMPATIBLE/PARTIAL/INCOMPATIBLE\\n    74→\\n    75→### Phase 4: Execution & Analysis\\n    76→\\n    77→Run the script and analyze:\\n    78→\\n    79→1. **Execute**: `chmod +x scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh && scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh --manual-live`\\n    80→2. **For each captured payload**: show command, artifact path, decoded JSON\\n    81→3. **Lifecycle mapping**: native hook name → Entire EventType\\n    82→4. **Field coverage**: which `Event` struct fields can be populated per event\\n    83→\\n    84→### Phase 5: Compatibility Report\\n    85→\\n    86→Generate structured markdown output directly to the user:\\n    87→\\n    88→```markdown\\n    89→# Agent Compatibility Report: $AGENT_NAME\\n    90→\\n    91→**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD\\n    92→**Agent:** $AGENT_NAME v$VERSION\\n    93→**Binary:** $AGENT_BIN\\n    94→**Verdict:** COMPATIBLE / PARTIAL / INCOMPATIBLE\\n    95→\\n    96→## Static Capability Checks\\n    97→\\n    98→| Check | Result | Notes |\\n    99→|-------|--------|-------|\\n   100→| Binary present | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n   101→| Help available | PASS/FAIL | |\\n   102→| Hook keywords found | PASS/WARN/FAIL | keywords found |\\n   103→| Session concept | PASS/WARN/FAIL | |\\n   104→| Config directory | PASS/WARN/FAIL | path |\\n   105→| Documentation | PASS/WARN/FAIL | URLs |\\n   106→\\n   107→## Lifecycle Event Mapping\\n   108→\\n   109→| Entire EventType | Native Hook | Status | Fields Available |\\n   110→|-----------------|-------------|--------|-----------------|\\n   111→| SessionStart | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\\n   112→| TurnStart | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\\n   113→| TurnEnd | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\\n   114→| Compaction | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\\n   115→| SessionEnd | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\\n   116→| SubagentStart | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\\n   117→| SubagentEnd | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\\n   118→\\n   119→## Required Interface Feasibility\\n   120→\\n   121→| Interface | Feasible | Complexity | Notes |\\n   122→|-----------|----------|------------|-------|\\n   123→| Agent (core) | Yes/No/Partial | Low/Med/High | |\\n   124→| HookSupport | Yes/No/Partial | Low/Med/High | |\\n   125→| TranscriptAnalyzer | Yes/No/Partial | Low/Med/High | |\\n   126→| TranscriptPreparer | Yes/No/N/A | Low/Med/High | |\\n   127→| TokenCalculator | Yes/No/N/A | Low/Med/High | |\\n   128→| SubagentAwareExtractor | Yes/No/N/A | Low/Med/High | |\\n   129→| FileWatcher | Yes/No/N/A | Low/Med/High | |\\n   130→\\n   131→## Integration Gaps\\n   132→\\n   133→1. **[HIGH/MED/LOW]** Description and impact\\n   134→2. ...\\n   135→\\n   136→## Recommended Adapter Approach\\n   137→\\n   138→- Which interfaces to impl