l, force bool) (int, error) { ... }\\n   178→func (a *Agent) UninstallHooks() error { ... }\\n   179→func (a *Agent) AreHooksInstalled() bool { ... }\\n   180→```\\n   181→\\n   182→Use the probe report to determine:\\n   183→- Which config file to modify (e.g., `.agent/settings.json`)\\n   184→- How hooks are registered (JSON objects, env vars, etc.)\\n   185→- What command format to use (`entire hooks $AGENT_SLUG <verb>`)\\n   186→\\n   187→Run: `mise run test`\\n   188→\\n   189→### Step 8: TDD Cycle — Transcript\\n   190→\\n   191→**Red**: Write `transcript_test.go`:\\n   192→\\n   193→```go\\n   194→func TestReadTranscript(t *testing.T) {\\n   195→    t.Parallel()\\n   196→    // Write sample transcript, read it back\\n   197→}\\n   198→\\n   199→func TestChunkTranscript(t *testing.T) {\\n   200→    t.Parallel()\\n   201→    // Test splitting large transcripts\\n   202→}\\n   203→```\\n   204→\\n   205→**Green**: Write `transcript.go` — implement `ReadTranscript`, `ChunkTranscript`, `ReassembleTranscript`.\\n   206→\\n   207→Use the probe report to understand the transcript format (JSONL, JSON, custom).\\n   208→\\n   209→Run: `mise run test`\\n   210→\\n   211→### Step 9: Optional Interfaces\\n   212→\\n   213→Based on the probe report's feasibility table, implement optional interfaces if applicable:\\n   214→\\n   215→- **TranscriptAnalyzer** — if the transcript format needs parsing for file extraction\\n   216→- **HookHandler** — if hooks need pre/post processing beyond ParseHookEvent\\n   217→- **TokenCalculator** — if the transcript contains token usage data\\n   218→- **SubagentAwareExtractor** — if the agent supports subagents/tasks\\n   219→- **FileWatcher** — if the agent doesn't have native hooks (like Gemini)\\n   220→\\n   221→Each follows the same TDD cycle: test first, implement, refactor.\\n   222→\\n   223→### Step 10: Register and Wire Up\\n   224→\\n   225→1. **Register hook commands**: Search `cmd/entire/cli/` for where hook subcommands are registered and add the new agent\\n   226→2. **Verify registration**: The `init()` function in `${AGENT_SLUG}.go` should call `agent.Register(agent.AgentName(\\\"$AGENT_SLUG\\\"), New)`\\n   227→3. **Run full test suite**: `mise run test:ci`\\n   228→\\n   229→### Step 11: Final Validation\\n   230→\\n   231→Run the complete validation:\\n   232→\\n   233→```bash\\n   234→mise run fmt      # Format\\n   235→mise run lint     # Lint\\n   236→mise run test:ci  # All tests (unit + integration)\\n   237→```\\n   238→\\n   239→Check against the integration checklist (`docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md`):\\n   240→\\n   241→- [ ] Full transcript stored at every checkpoint\\n   242→- [ ] Native format preserved\\n   243→- [ ] All mappable hook events implemented\\n   244→- [ ] Session storage working\\n   245→- [ ] Hook installation/uninstallation working\\n   246→- [ ] Tests pass with `t.Parallel()`\\n   247→\\n   248→## Key Patterns to Follow\\n   249→\\n   250→- **Use `agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[T]`** for parsing hook stdin JSON\\n   251→- **Use `paths.WorktreeRoot()`** not `os.Getwd()` for git-relative paths\\n   252→- **Preserve unknown config keys** when modifying agent config files (don't clobber user settings)\\n   253→- **Use `logging.Debug/Info/Warn/Error`** for internal logging, not `fmt.Print`\\n   254→- **Keep interface implementations minimal** — only implement what's needed\\n   255→- **Follow Go idioms** from `.golangci.yml` — check before writing code\\n   256→\\n   257→## Output\\n   258→\\n   259→Summarize what was implemented:\\n   260→- Package directory and files created\\n   261→- Interfaces implemented (core + optional)\\n   262→- Hook names registered\\n   263→- Test coverage (number of test functions, what they cover)\\n   264→- Any gaps or TODOs remaining\\n   265→- Commands to run full validation\\n   266→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"d462b025-c944-4c75-9d50-265cf2743f8f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T21:42:52.569Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\