"merry-leaping-turing\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01MDtKj2AnvjQFj71zMCCHYR\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Probe Command\\n     2→\\n     3→Assess whether a target AI coding agent's hook/lifecycle model is compatible with the Entire CLI before writing any Go code.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Procedure\\n     6→\\n     7→### Phase 1: Architecture Inspection\\n     8→\\n     9→Read these repo files to understand the Entire lifecycle model that the agent must integrate with:\\n    10→\\n    11→**Required reading:**\\n    12→\\n    13→1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — The `Agent` interface (core methods + 6 optional capability interfaces)\\n    14→2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — 7 normalized EventTypes: `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\n    15→3. `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` — How native hook names are registered and routed\\n    16→4. `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — `DispatchLifecycleEvent` handler\\n    17→5. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Full implementation guide\\n    18→6. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Validation criteria\\n    19→\\n    20→**Reference implementations** (read 1-2 for patterns):\\n    21→\\n    22→- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/` — Most complete, has all optional interfaces\\n    23→- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/` — File-watcher based hook model\\n    24→- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/` — Plugin-based hook model\\n    25→\\n    26→Focus on `types.go` (hook input structs), `lifecycle.go` (ParseHookEvent), and `hooks.go` (HookSupport) in each.\\n    27→\\n    28→### Phase 2: Static Capability Checks\\n    29→\\n    30→Non-destructive CLI probing. Record PASS/WARN/FAIL for each:\\n    31→\\n    32→| Check | Command | PASS | FAIL |\\n    33→|-------|---------|------|------|\\n    34→| Binary present | `command -v $AGENT