e them entirely, or keep them but with \\\"read the actual interface\\\" caveats?\\n4. What's the right balance between \\\"here's exactly what to read\\\" vs \\\"go discover\\\"?\\n\\nPlease design an approach that makes the skill resilient to codebase evolution without making it so vague that it loses its utility as a guide.\",\"agentId\":\"ae4ef6893ab163f47\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01Wvr31ojKCuADWh32JSR2Vb\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01PWEmt8g1qUDtEZEfbD68F3\",\"uuid\":\"ce81d18d-5e1d-4154-be03-84944c5c2137\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T21:50:01.975Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ce81d18d-5e1d-4154-be03-84944c5c2137\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"e3b9b251-e322-4a6b-b48d-361a9097e77a\",\"version\":\"2.1.53\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/agent-integration-skill\",\"slug\":\"merry-leaping-turing\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_016HHU4wB2mbF2mDi7csrxtr\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Agent Integration Checklist\\n     2→\\n     3→This document provides requirements and a checklist for integrating new AI coding agents with Entire. Use this to validate your implementation is correct and complete.\\n     4→\\n     5→For step-by-step implementation instructions, code templates, and testing patterns, see the [Agent Implementation Guide](agent-guide.md).\\n     6→\\n     7→## Core Principle: Full Transcript Storage\\n     8→\\n     9→Entire stores the **complete session transcript** at every checkpoint, not incremental diffs. This enables:\\n    10→\\n    11→- Simple rewind: restore the full transcript, agent resumes from that state\\n    12→- No dependency on previous checkpoints being intact\\n    13→- Consistent behavior across all checkpoint types (committed, uncommitted)\\n    14→\\n    15→**Each checkpoint must contain the full session history up to that point.**\\n    16→\\n    17→## Core Principle: Native Format Preservation\\n    18→\\n    19→Store transcripts in the **agent's native format**. Any transformation or normalization should only be done to support CLI features (rewind, resume, summarization, file extraction), not for backend or web UI consumption.\\n    20→\\n    21→**Why:**\\n    22→- The backend/web UI should handle format differences, not the CLI\\n    23→- Transforming for downstream consumers couples the CLI to their requirements\\n    24→- Native formats ensure compatibility with agent's own import/export tools\\n    25→- Reduces risk of data loss from lossy transformations\\n    26→- Format changes that break the UI can be fixed with a backend deploy; CLI changes require a full release cycle and user adoption\\n    27→\\n    28→**Do:**\\n    29→- Store the raw transcript as the agent produces it\\n    30→- Parse the native format when CLI features need specific data (e.g., extract file paths for `entire status`)\\n    31→- Let the backend normalize formats for display\\n    32→\\n    33→**Don't:**\\n    34→- Create a \\\"universal transcript format\\\" in the CLI\\n    35→- Transform logs to match what the web UI expects\\n    36→- Strip or restructure data to simplify backend processing\\n    37→- Create intermediate formats (e.g., converting JSON to JSONL for \\\"easier parsing\\\")\\n    38→- Reconstruct transcripts from events when a canonical export exists\\n    39→\\n    40→## Integration Checklist\\n    41→\\n    42→### Transcript Capture\\n    43→\\n    44→See Guide: [Transcript Format Guide](agent-guide.md#transcript-format-guide), [TranscriptAnalyzer](agent-guide.md#transcriptanalyzer), [TranscriptPreparer](agent-guide.md#transcriptpreparer)\\n    45→\\n    46→- [ ] **Full transcript on every turn**: At turn-end, capture the complete session transcript, not just events since the last checkpoint\\n    47→- [ ] **Resumed session handling**: When a user resumes an existing session, the transcript must include all historical messages, not just new ones since the plugin/hook loaded\\n    48→- [ ] **Use agent's canonical export**: Prefer the agent's native export command (e.g., reading Claude's JSONL file, Gemini's JSON) over manually reconstructing from events\\n    49→- [ ] **No custom formats**: Store the agent's native format directly in `NativeData` - do not convert between formats (e.g., JSON to JSONL) or create intermediate representations\\n    50→- [ ] **Graceful degradation**: If the canonical source is unavailable (e.g., agent shutting down), fall back to best-effort capture with clear documentation of limitations\\n    51→\\n    52→### Session Storage Abstraction\\n    53→\\n    54→See Guide: [Step 3 - Core Agent Interface](agent-guide.md#step-3-implement-core-agent-interface-youragentgo)\\n    55→\\n    56→- [ ] **`WriteSession` implementation**: Agent must implement `WriteSession(AgentSession)` to restore sessions\\n    57→- [ ] **File-based agents** (Claude, Gemini): Write `NativeData` to `SessionRef` path\\n    58→- [ ] **Database-backed agents**: Write `NativeData` to file, then import into native storage (the native format should be what the agent's import command expects)\\n    59→- [ ] **Single format per agent**: Store only the agent's native format in `NativeData` - no separate fields for different representations of the same data\\n    60→\\n    61→### Hook Events\\n    62→\\n    63→See Guide: [Step 4 - ParseHookEvent](agent-guide.md#step-4-implement-parsehookevent-lifecyclego), [Event Mapping Reference](agent-guide.md#event-mapping-reference)\\n    64→\\n    65→Map agent-native hooks to these `EventType` constants (see `agent/event.go`):\\n    66→\\n    67→- [ ] **TurnStart**: Fire when user submits a prompt (for pre-prompt state capture)\\n    68→- [ ] **TurnEnd**: Fire when agent finishes responding (for checkpoint creation)\\n    69→- [ ] **SessionStart**: Fire when a new session begins\\n    70→- [ ] **SessionEnd**: Fire when session is explicitly ended (optional but recommended)\\n    71→\\n    72→### Rewind/Resume Support\\n    73→\\n    74→- [ ] **Rewind restores full state**: After rewind, agent can continue from that point with full context\\n    75→- [ ] **Resume command**: `FormatResumeCommand()` returns the CLI command to resume a session\\n    76→- [ ] **Session ID preservation**: Restored sessions maintain original session ID where possible\\n    77→\\n    78→### Testing\\n    79→\\n    80→See Guide: [Testing Patterns](agent-guide.md#testing-patterns)\\n    81→\\n    82→- [ ] **New session**: Create session, multiple turns, verify full transcript at each checkpoint\\n    83→- [ ] **Resumed session**: Resume existing session, add turns, verify checkpoint includes historical messages\\n    84→- [ ] **Rewind**: Rewind to earlier checkpoint, verify agent can continue from that state\\n    85→- [ ] **Agent shutdown**: Verify graceful handling if agent exits during checkpoint\\n    86→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"ed140fb6-f7e2-4da3-8322-1661a107271c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T21:50:01.980Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"I need to redesign agent-integration skill files to be less dependent on exact file paths, reducing maintenance burden when the codebase evolves.\\n\\n## Current state\\nThe skill has 4 prompt files under `.claude/skills/agent-integration/`:\\n- `README.md` — overview with 6 paths\\n- `probe-prompt.md` — probe phase, 13 paths + hardcoded event type names\\n- `e2e-test-prompt.md` — E2E test generation, 16 paths + hardcoded runner/test file names  \\n- `implement-prompt.md` — TDD implementation, 14 paths + hardcoded method signatures\\n\\n## Types of hardcoded references that cause drift\\n\\n1. **\\\"Required reading\\\" lists** — Numbered lists of exact file paths that must be read before starting. Example from probe-prompt.md:\\n```\\n1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — The `Agent` interface\\n2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — 7 normalized EventTypes\\n3.