ditionally, `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — which the skill prompts reference as authoritative — is itself severely drifted: it lists deleted methods (`HookHandler`, `GetSupportedHooks`, `SupportsHooks`, `GetHookConfigPath`, `ParseHookInput`), says \\\"19 methods\\\" when there are 15, and uses the renamed `paths.RepoRoot()` instead of `paths.WorktreeRoot()`.\\n\\n**Approach: \\\"Anchor + Discover\\\"** — Keep stable file paths as entry points, but replace enumerated details with instructions for the AI agent to discover them from source code using its tools (Read, Glob, Grep).\\n\\n## Scope Decision\\n\\nThe skill prompts and `agent-guide.md` are tightly coupled — the prompts delegate to the guide as the authoritative source. Fixing only the prompts while the guide remains wrong would leave the agent following incorrect instructions.\\n\\n**In scope:**\\n- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/probe-prompt.md` — replace enumerations with discovery\\n- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/e2e-test-prompt.md` — replace enumerations with discovery\\n- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implement-prompt.md` — replace code examples with \\\"read the interface\\\" + remove duplicate template code (the guide already has full templates)\\n- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/README.md` — minor: make agent listing discoverable\\n- `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — fix stale method table, remove deleted interfaces, update `paths.RepoRoot()` → `paths.WorktreeRoot()`, add caveat about verifying signatures\\n\\n**Out of scope:**\\n- `SKILL.md` — no volatile references\\n- `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — not inspected, may need separate pass\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Fix drift (prerequisite for other changes)\\n\\n**Quick Reference table (lines 19-42):** The table lists methods that no longer exist on the Agent interface.\\n- Remove `GetHookConfigPath()`, `SupportsHooks()`, `ParseHookInput()` — these are legacy/removed\\n- Remove `HookNames()` and `ParseHookEvent()` — these are on `HookSupport`, not `Agent`\\n- Add `IsPreview()` — exists on Agent but missing from table\\n- Change \\\"19 methods\\\" to \\\"15 methods\\\" or remove count entirely\\n- Regroup to match actual interface: Identity (6) + Transcript (3) + Legacy (6)\\n\\n**Optional Interfaces table (lines 45-53):**\\n- Remove `HookHandler` row (interface doesn't exist) and `GetSupportedHooks` from `HookSupport` row\\n- Move `HookNames` and `ParseHookEvent` into the `HookSupport` row (that's where they live)\\n- Update `HookSupport` method list to: `HookNames`, `ParseHookEvent`, `InstallHooks`, `UninstallHooks`, `AreHooksInstalled`\\n\\n**Code templates (lines 123-223, 230-312, 374-406):**\\n- Replace all `paths.RepoRoot()` with `paths.WorktreeRoot()`\\n- Remove `HookHandler` compile-time assertion (line 365)\\n- Remove `GetSupportedHooks` method from Step 8 code (line 405)\\n- Add caveat at top of guide: \\\"Method signatures shown here are illustrative. Always verify against the actual interface in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go`.\\\"\\n\\n**Test file references (lines 726-731):** Replace enumeration of specific test files with:\\n```\\nRun `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/lifecycle_test.go\\\")` and similar patterns to find reference test files.\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `probe-prompt.md` — 4 changes\\n\\n**Required reading (lines 12-18):** Remove inline enumerations, keep file anchors.\\n```\\n1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — Read to find the `Agent` interface and all optional capability interfaces\\n2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — Read to find all `EventType` constants (the normalized lifecycle events agents must map to)\\n3. `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` — How native hook names are registered and routed\\n4. `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — `DispatchLifecycleEvent` handler\\n5. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Full implementation guide\\n6. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Validation criteria\\n```\\n\\n**Reference implementations (lines 21-26):** Replace specific agent listings with discovery.\\n```\\n**Reference implementations:** Run `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")` to discover all existing agent packages. Pick 1-2 as reference. In each, focus on `lifecycle.go` (ParseHookEvent), `hooks.go` (HookSupport), and `types.go` (hook input structs).\\n```\\n\\n**Compatibility report template — EventType table (lines 110-118):** Replace hardcoded rows with dynamic instruction.\\n```\\n## Lifecycle Event Mapping\\n\\nFor each EventType constant found in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go`, create a row:\\n\\n| Entire EventType | Native Hook | Status | Fields Available |\\n|-----------------|-------------|--------|-----------------|\\n| (one row per EventType from event.go) | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\\n```\\n\\n**Compatibility report template — Interface feasibility table (lines 122-131):** Replace hardcoded rows with dynamic instruction.\\n```\\n## Required Interface Feasibility\\n\\nFor each interface defined in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go`, assess feasibility:\\n\\n| Interface | Feasible | Complexity | Notes |\\n|-----------|----------|------------|-------|\\n| Agent (core) | Yes/No/Partial | Low/Med/High | |\\n| (one row per optional interface from agent.go) | ... | ... | |\\n```\\n\\n### 3. `e2e-test-prompt.md` — 3 changes\\n\\n**Step 1 — infrastructure files (lines 15-20):** Keep the 5 structural file names (stable infrastructure), but remove inline enumeration of runner class names.\\n```\\n3. `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/agent_runner.go` — `AgentRunner` interface and existing runner implementations. Read the file to discover all current runners and the `NewAgentRunner` factory.\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2 — scenario tests (lines 24-31):** Replace exhaustive file list with glob discovery.\\n```\\n### Step 2: Read Existing E2E Scenario Tests\\n\\nRun `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/scenario_*_test.go\\\")` to find all existing scenario tests. Read each