a for completeness.\\n3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — Read to find the exact `Agent` interface and all optional interfaces.\\n4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — Read to find `EventType` constants and shared parsing helpers.\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2 — reference implementation table (lines 25-31):** Replace with discovery.\\n```\\n### Step 2: Read Reference Implementation\\n\\nRun `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")` to find all existing agent packages. Pick the closest match based on probe findings — read a few agents' `hooks.go` files to find one with a similar hook mechanism to your target. Read all `*.go` files (skip `*_test.go` on first pass) in the chosen reference.\\n```\\n\\n**Steps 4-9 — TDD cycles (lines 43-221):** Replace inline code examples with \\\"read the interface + reference\\\" instructions. The `agent-guide.md` already has comprehensive code templates — the skill prompts should not duplicate them.\\n\\nFor each TDD step, the pattern becomes:\\n```\\n**Green**: Create `${file}.go`. Read the relevant interface in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` for exact method signatures. Read the corresponding file in a reference agent (find via `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/${file}.go\\\")`) for the implementation pattern. The `agent-guide.md` has a complete code template if needed.\\n```\\n\\nSpecifically:\\n- Step 5 (core agent): Remove the `init()` + struct + method stub code block. Replace with: \\\"Read Agent interface in agent.go for all methods. Read agent-guide.md Step 3 for the full code template. Use `agent.Register(agent.AgentName(\\\"$AGENT_SLUG\\\"), New)` in init().\\\"\\n- Step 6 (lifecycle): Remove the ParseHookEvent code block. Replace with: \\\"Read HookSupport interface in agent.go. Read agent-guide.md Step 4 for the switch-case pattern.\\\"\\n- Step 7 (hooks): Remove the InstallHooks/UninstallHooks/AreHooksInstalled stubs. Replace with: \\\"Read HookSupport interface in agent.go for exact signatures. Read agent-guide.md Step 8 for installation pattern.\\\"\\n- Step 8 (transcript): Remove code block. Replace with: \\\"Read TranscriptAnalyzer interface in agent.go. Read agent-guide.md Transcript Format Guide for JSONL vs JSON patterns.\\\"\\n- Step 9 (optional interfaces): Remove bullet list of interface names. Replace with: \\\"Read agent.go for all optional interfaces. For each one the probe report marked as feasible, follow the same TDD cycle.\\\"\\n\\n**Step 10 — register (lines 223-226):** Already uses discovery (\\\"Search cmd/entire/cli/ for...\\\"). Keep as-is.\\n\\n### 5. `README.md` — 1 change\\n\\n**Line 50:** Replace hardcoded agent list with discovery pattern.\\n```\\n- Existing agents: Discover via `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")`\\n```\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Changes | Risk |\\n|------|---------|------|\\n| `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` | Fix stale methods, update paths, add caveat | Medium — large file, many code blocks |\\n| `.claude/skills/agent-integration/probe-prompt.md` | Replace 4 enumerated sections with discovery | Low |\\n| `.claude/skills/agent-integration/e2e-test-prompt.md` | Replace 3 enumerated sections with discovery | Low |\\n| `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implement-prompt.md` | Remove 6 code blocks, replace with read-the-source instructions | Medium — largest structural change |\\n| `.claude/skills/agent-integration/README.md` | 1-line change | Low |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `grep -rn 'factoryaidroid\\\\|FactoryAIDroid' .claude/skills/ docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — should return nothing\\n2. `grep -rn 'paths\\\\.RepoRoot' docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — should return nothing after fix\\n3. `grep -rn 'HookHandler\\\\|GetSupportedHooks' docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — should return nothing after fix\\n4. `grep -rn '19 method' docs/architecture/agent-guide.md .claude/skills/` — should return nothing\\n5. Read each modified file end-to-end to verify markdown renders correctly (no unclosed fences)\\n6. Verify each skill pr